TITLE: Kalki Avatar | Grp Member Ruchi Goyal Experience With Adi Parashakti Noor Ananta Ji
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QRmoGvnuy7U
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
Ruchi Goyal shares her profound journey of connecting with Adi Parashakti Noor Ananta. She begins with deep reverence, expressing gratitude for being chosen. Her spiritual journey truly began after the 2020 COVID lockdown, aligning with what Baba describes as the birth/descent of Kalki during that period. She started with randomly listening to meditation music and gradually progressed step by step through divine grace, joining many meditation groups but never finding satisfaction.

She discovered Noor Baba through Rakesh Sharma's YouTube channel, and was deeply attracted by Baba's eyes. She wanted to keep listening and tried to decode Baba's messages despite having no formal spiritual knowledge. She never stayed with any guru before, as she always felt they were exploitative, and believed her destined guru would find her. In 2024, a WhatsApp group invitation came but she lacked the courage to join. She deeply regretted missing that chance. In January 2025, she overcame her fear and joined.

In just four months, her life underwent drastic positive changes -- she gained confidence she never had, found self-love, recognized her inner strength, and learned to embrace her shortcomings. She received a divine vision of Shiv-Shakti at Baba's feet, and later had a vision of her own soul, describing it as extraordinarily beautiful. She emphasizes that the divine is found within oneself, and Baba is showering nothing but love upon everyone.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- Spiritual journey activated post-COVID 2020, confirming Kalki's descent timeline
- Attracted by Baba's eyes through YouTube; felt an inexplicable pull despite no formal spiritual training
- Had a divine vision (darshan) of Shiv-Shakti at Baba's feet
- Experienced a vision of her own soul, describing it as incredibly beautiful
- Complete personality transformation from a girl with zero self-confidence to someone who speaks openly

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: Divine Experience

